---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const seo = {
  title: "Mubu — Your Wellness Buddy | Anna Kocaj",
  description:
    "How I designed a gamified wellness app in a 24-hour hackathon, winning 3rd place with a fully playable prototype.",
  image: "/mubu.png",
};
---

<Layout seo={seo}>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <a
      href="/projects"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-sm mb-8"
    >
      ← Back to projects
    </a>

    <p class="text-sm opacity-50 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3 font-medium">
      Case Study · October 2024
    </p>
    <h1 class="font-bold text-3xl mb-4 leading-snug">
      Mubu — Your Wellness Buddy
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg opacity-70 mb-8 max-w-xl leading-relaxed">
      A gamified wellness app designed to make emotional wellbeing accessible
      through quick, playful micro-habits. Built in a <strong
        >24-hour hackathon</strong
      > and awarded <strong>3rd place</strong>.
    </p>

    <!-- Overview grid -->
    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-4 py-6 border-t border-b border-white/10 mb-10"
    >
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Role</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">UX / Product Designer</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">
          Timeline
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">24 hours</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Format</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">Hackathon</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Tools</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium">Figma</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero image -->
    <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden mb-16 bg-gray-800">
      <Image
        src="/mubu.png"
        alt="Mubu wellness app screens"
        width={1200}
        height={675}
        class="w-full object-cover"
      />
      <p class="text-xs opacity-30 text-center py-2">
        Placeholder — replace with final mockup or Behance export
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CHALLENGE -->
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-4">The Challenge</h2>
    <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      The hackathon brief asked teams to design a product that could improve
      mental wellness for everyday users. The challenge wasn't the subject
      matter — it was the constraint: a fully playable, persuasive prototype in
      24 hours that could compete against teams with engineers building real
      code.
    </p>
    <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed">
      Existing wellness apps are often heavy, lecture-y, or demand long daily
      commitments. The opportunity was to design something that could slot into
      a 2-minute gap in someone's day and still feel meaningful.
    </p>
    <div
      class="mt-8 p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-sm opacity-50"
    >
      <!-- TODO: Add hackathon brief or insight quote if available -->
      📌 <em>Placeholder: Add brief, HMW statement, or key research insight</em>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROCESS -->
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-8">Process</h2>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          01 — Define
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">
          Framing the problem under time pressure
        </h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          With only 24 hours, I front-loaded the framing. We aligned quickly on
          a core user: someone who wants to manage stress or low mood but doesn't
          have the headspace for a structured programme. The north star became:
          <em>"One small thing, right now, that actually helps."</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          02 — Concept
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">
          Gamification as an engagement hook
        </h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          Rather than tracking or reporting (which can amplify anxiety), Mubu
          centres on a companion character that grows and responds as the user
          completes micro-activities: journaling prompts, breathing exercises,
          and a quick mood check-in. Progress is visible but gentle — no streaks
          to break, no failure states.
        </p>
        <div
          class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-sm opacity-50"
        >
          <!-- TODO: Add concept sketches or early wireframes -->
          📌 <em>Placeholder: Add concept sketches or early wireframes</em>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div>
        <p
          class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-2 font-medium"
        >
          03 — Design & Prototype
        </p>
        <h3 class="font-medium text-base mb-3">
          Shipping a fully playable prototype
        </h3>
        <p class="opacity-70 leading-relaxed text-sm">
          I designed and prototyped all screens in Figma — including the
          companion interactions, activity flows, and onboarding — within the
          24-hour window. The prototype was interactive enough for judges to
          experience the full core loop without any explanation.
        </p>
        <div
          class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-sm opacity-50"
        >
          <!-- TODO: Add final UI screens (export from Behance or Figma) -->
          📌 <em>Placeholder: Add final UI screens</em>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUTCOMES -->
  <section class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-semibold text-xl mb-6">Outcomes</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">3rd</p>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-60">place out of all competing teams</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">24h</p>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-60">from brief to playable prototype</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5">
        <p class="text-3xl font-bold mb-1">100%</p>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-60">Figma — no engineering required</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="opacity-60 text-sm leading-relaxed">
      The project also demonstrated the value of clear concept framing under
      pressure: the judges specifically noted the product narrative as a
      standout strength.
    </p>
    <div
      class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/5 text-sm opacity-50"
    >
      <!-- TODO: Add judge quote, team photo, or Behance link as a reference -->
      📌 <em
        >Placeholder: Add judge feedback or link to full Behance case study</em
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NAVIGATION -->
  <section
    class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 mb-16 flex justify-between items-center border-t border-white/10 pt-8"
  >
    <a
      href="/projects/rekord24"
      class="opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-sm"
    >
      ← Rekord24
    </a>
    <a
      href="/projects/apteczka"
      class="opacity-50 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-sm"
    >
      Next: Apteczka →
    </a>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  strong {
    color: white;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  em {
    color: inherit;
  }
</style>
